.TH getpid 2
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lgetpid\*O, \*Lgetpgrp\*O, \*Lgetppid\*O \- Gets the process ID, process group ID, parent process ID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <unistd.h>
.PP
\*L#include <sys/types.h>
.PP
\*Lpid_t getpid( void );
.PP
\*Lpid_t getpgrp( void );
.PP
\*Lpid_t getppid( void );
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "getpid function"
.iX "getpgrp function"
.iX "getppid function"
.iX "process ID" "returning"
.iX "group ID" "returning for a process"
.iX "parent process ID" "returning"
.iX "process" "returning ID"
.iX "process" "returning group ID"
.iX "process" "returning parent process ID"
The \*Lgetpid(\|)\*O
function returns the process ID of the calling process.
.PP
\*OThe \*Lgetpgrp(\|)\*O
function returns the process group ID of the calling process.
.PP
\*OThe \*Lgetppid(\|)\*O
function returns the parent process ID of the calling process.
When a process is created, its parent process ID is the process ID of
its parent process.  If a parent process exits, the parent process IDs of
its child processes are changed to the process ID of
\*Linit\*O.
.SH NOTES
.PP
.VL 1.5i
.LI "\*LAES Support Level:\*O"
Full use
.LE
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
System calls:
\*Lfork\*O(2),
\*Lkill\*O(2),
\*Lsetpgid\*O(2),
\*Lsetsid\*O(2),
\*Lwait\*O(2)
.iX "getpid function"
.iX "getpgrp function"
.iX "getppid function"
.EQ
